  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" English songs is subjective and varies greatly based on personal taste, genre preference, and cultural significance. However, some songs are widely regarded as classics or have had a significant impact on music and culture. Here\u2019s a list of a few notable English songs across various genres:\n\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" - Queen**\n2. **\"Imagine\" - John Lennon**\n3. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" - Led Zeppelin**\n4. **\"Billie Jean\" - Michael Jackson**\n5. **\"Hotel California\" - Eagles**\n6. **\"Hey Jude\" - The Beatles**\n7. **\"Rolling in the Deep\" - Adele**\n8. **\"Like a Rolling Stone\" - Bob Dylan**\n9. **\"I Will Always Love You\" - Whitney Houston**\n10. **\"Shape of You\" - Ed Sheeran**\n\nThese songs showcase a mix of rock, pop, and soul and have left a lasting influence on music history. What are some of your favorite songs?",
